<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[121,760,818,983]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
<taxonomicName box="[121,400,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[121,400,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">Lentilactobacillus hilgardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(hil.gar’di.i. N.L. gen. n. 
<taxonomicName box="[672,760,897,921]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lentilactobacillus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[672,760,897,921]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">hilgardii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of Hilgard, named after E.W. Hilgard, a pioneer of enology in the State of California, USA).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[121,762,1005,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
Basonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="Douglas and Cruess 1936" authorityName="Douglas and Cruess" authorityYear="1936" box="[235,756,1005,1029]" class="Bacilli" family="Lactobacillaceae" genus="Lactobacillus" kingdom="Bacteria" order="Lactobacillales" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" phylum="Firmicutes" rank="species" species="hilgardii">
<emphasis box="[235,468,1005,1029]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">Lactobacillus hilgardii</emphasis>
Douglas and Cruess 1936
</taxonomicName>
, 115 (Approved Lists); the species was initially described in 1936; the description was emended in 1949 after the original type strain was lost [
<bibRefCitation author="Douglas HC &amp; Cruess W." box="[336,379,1098,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref74087" refString="330. Douglas HC, Cruess W. A Lactobacillus from California wine: Lactobacillus hilgardii. J Food Sci 1936; 1: 113 - 119." type="journal article" year="1936">330</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vaughn RH &amp; Douglas HC &amp; Fornachon JCM" box="[390,431,1098,1122]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="133 - 139" refId="ref74115" refString="331. Vaughn RH, Douglas HC, Fornachon JCM. The taxonomy of Lactobacillus hilgardii and related heterofermentative lactobacilli. Hilgardia 1949; 19: 133 - 139." type="journal article" year="1949">331</bibRefCitation>
]
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[121,762,1144,1230]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845">
Strains grow optimally between pH 4.5 and 5.5 and in the range of 15 to 40 °C [
<bibRefCitation author="Douglas HC &amp; Cruess W." box="[349,392,1175,1199]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="113 - 119" refId="ref74087" refString="330. Douglas HC, Cruess W. A Lactobacillus from California wine: Lactobacillus hilgardii. J Food Sci 1936; 1: 113 - 119." type="journal article" year="1936">330</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vaughn RH &amp; Douglas HC &amp; Fornachon JCM" box="[403,446,1175,1199]" pageId="63" pageNumber="2845" pagination="133 - 139" refId="ref74115" refString="331. Vaughn RH, Douglas HC, Fornachon JCM. The taxonomy of Lactobacillus hilgardii and related heterofermentative lactobacilli. Hilgardia 1949; 19: 133 - 139." type="journal article" year="1949">331</bibRefCitation>
]. Thegenome size of the type strain is 2.60 Mbp. The mol% G+C content of DNA is 39.6.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
